USE THIS.description: Dutch Lane is an unmarked path located above Bowen Road and below Peak Road in Hong Kong. In the past, it was used by Dutch people to travel from their homes to their workplaces at a Dutch shipping line.

The Shing Mun Redoubt is a historic military fortification from the 1930s that protected Hong Kong from land-based attacks. It was an important defense during World War II, but the Japanese overtook it in December 1941.
